Global Auto companies began to unite, dozens of China's hundreds of auto manufacturing enterprises situation will be broken. It's harder for small companies to survive. Big companies have merger bonuses. Online sales of vehicles and other new channels new forms of business can be expected

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo / China News

##

By Wang Binbin and Li Xinyin, CAIJING reporters

Editor | Shi Zhiliang

Empty streets, the door can be empty of 4s shop out of the current Chinese car market cold.

The precipitous drop in retail sales in the first two weeks of February 2020, down 92 percent year-on-year, has shaken the confidence of car companies and dealers, "it's easy to get into trouble if this keeps up, " one dealer told Caijing, a lot of businesses are going to collapse.

The disruption of the rally that started in the fourth quarter of 2019 has made many experts in the industry even more pessimistic about China's auto market in 2020, with predictions of a decline of 2% , 5% or even 10% . The government also began to bail out the market, and the Commerce Department said it would boost car consumption.

The market can be pessimistic, should not despair, auto e-commerce, online car, live car sales and other new channels of new business began to sprout, the car industry integration resistance in the cold winter will be much less. After all that, isn't this an opportunity?

The frozen car market

Sitting in his office on the second floor, the general manager of a luxury car dealership in Shanghai peered through a window grate into the showroom, demoralizing his returning staff. Although, Shanghai has been sunny, but consumers still have fear, mouth read safety first, one day down the shop customers are still few.

"A lot of companies will not survive this wave, " he sighed over the phone and told Caijing, referring to the operating costs, including Labor, as well as the capital accumulation behind the inventory of vehicles.

Dealers are right to be concerned. Retail sales in the first two weeks of February 2020 were largely frozen, with sales of 811 vehicles per day in the first week and 4,098 in the second, a 92 percent drop from the previous two weeks, according to the federation.

Dealers across the country opened in small numbers, with little foot traffic, and consumers bought cars during the outbreak only when there was a particularly urgent need.

It's not just consumers. Dealers want safety. A state-owned background dealer sales person-in-charge said frankly, compared to making money, "the store do not have the most important thing. ". During this period, the shop on duty system, the intention to reduce the gathering of personnel.

To satisfy the authorities, the dealer's storefront has been closed, allowing customers to enter only through side doors, which require a "shot to the forehead" .

The official said, now everyone with a "minimum income" to live, just understand what is called "Black Swan" , normal daily cash flow is too important.

In this context, there are consumers trying to "make it worse" . "All of us are helping to make collection calls, " an employee of an auto finance company in a mainframe factory told Caijing. He had made nearly 200 calls, mostly from customers who were not long overdue, placate them and insist on regular payments.

In his view, the car loan companies are most afraid of someone in a deliberate "whacking" , malicious overdue loans, trying to drag down the company in order to escape recovery. At the end of the day, he was also angry, some clients in the name of the country let me stay at home, refused to pay the loan on schedule, said with justification.

Sales are struggling and car production capacity is falling. As of Feb. 12,59 of China's 183 vehicle production bases had resumed production, accounting for 32.2 percent, according to the China Association of Automobile Manufacturers. Since then, more carmakers have returned to work, but with much less capacity.

An employee of one of the top three auto companies in China told CAIJING that their factory resumed work, but the factory was reduced from three shifts to one shift due to the fact that the anti-epidemic needs can not be crowded, sales and other factors.

UBS Auto Industry analyst Gong Min expects China's auto production capacity to drop 20 percent or more in the first quarter of this year due to a reduction in working days, uncertainty about when workers will return to work and the impact on the supply chain.

The SARS outbreak

The new pneumonia outbreak is reminiscent of the SARS epidemic in 2003.

In 2003, the SARS epidemic triggered people's yearning for the safety of private travel space. The car market grew by nearly 70% in the second quarter and more than 50% in the third quarter.

Well, that was then, this is now. With only 24 million cars in China 17 years ago and a first-time purchase rate of more than 95 percent, public awareness of the safety of private car travel has accelerated the explosion of car consumption in China. Today, more than 20 million cars are sold a year, and a significantly higher proportion of consumers switch to new cars and buy them back. Compared with the post-SARS era, cars are no longer a necessity.

As Yasunaga partner Ye Liang said, the second and third quarters may see a wave of demand rebound and release, as the safety and convenience of private cars are taken seriously, but today's increase in consumption does not mean a reversal of the explosion, the epidemic will still do more harm than good to the auto market as a whole in 2020.

The CAA's findings are similarly grim. The CAA said it has surveyed more than 300 vehicle and parts companies, but a comprehensive analysis of the feedback shows that the short-term impact of the epidemic on China's economy is greater than that of SARS in 2003, the impact on the auto industry, which was in a period of adjustment, was even greater.

The car market in 2020 could get worse as a result of the epidemic.

In the fourth quarter of 2019, China's auto market showed signs of rebounding from nearly two years of decline. But this time the upturn was interrupted by an outbreak.

Specifically, February 2019 is the Spring Festival, and January 2020 is the Spring Festival. If there was no outbreak, it would have been a year on year fall in January and a year on year rise in February. But affected by the outbreak, the secretary-general of the China Federation of automobile industry, Cui Dongshu, said the january-february affected by the outbreak, China's car market may fall by 25-30% .

Chang'an motor's executive vice president also said that if the outbreak was brought under control by the end of the first quarter, the market began to recover gradually in april-june and narrow passenger cars were expected to fall about 5 per cent year-on-year.

Benne said new car sales are expected to remain flat for the year if the outbreak ends in the first quarter and consumers in the service sector and small and medium enterprises lose their spending power, despite additional positive factors such as policy New-car sales could face a 10 per cent or more decline in a bearish scenario if the epidemic lasts longer, putting further pressure on the overall economy and spending power.

At the same time, trade associations are calling for new policies. The China Association of Automobile Dealers Calls for the lifting of restrictions on buying and driving in some cities, as well as boosting second-hand car sales to boost new car sales. The China Association of Automobile Industry has suggested to the relevant departments that the six emission standards be implemented nationwide.

Earlier, Gong Min told Caijing that he did not expect the government to introduce a particularly strong policy to stimulate auto consumption. But as a result, he underestimated the importance of the auto industry, and the bail-out began to roll out.

On February 20, Wang Bin, Deputy Director-general of the Department of Market Operations of the Ministry of Commerce, said at a press conference that, will thoroughly implement the Central Committee's important decision-making and deployment on "actively stabilizing traditional large-scale consumption such as automobiles" and the spirit of the State Council General Office's opinions on accelerating development and circulation and promoting commercial consumption, will work with the relevant departments to study the introduction of further stabilization of automobile consumption policy measures to reduce the impact of the epidemic on automobile consumption.

At the same time, local governments are encouraged to adopt measures to promote consumption of new-energy vehicles, increase the quota for traditional vehicle purchases and carry out measures such as exchanging old vehicles for new ones, so as to promote automobile consumption according to local conditions.

But such statements and policies are a drop in the bucket, and if the outbreak is not effectively contained in the short term, the markets and professionals now call for more and stronger policies may be on the way.

Looking for an opportunity in a crisis

"On a Spring Festival when the roads are empty and the weather is still foggy, can you please stop making cars take the blame? " said a US car dealer in Tianjin. Despite the support from manufacturers, in the final analysis, open source is the most important thing.

The main engine factory helps the dealer to overcome the difficulties by adjusting the performance appraisal mechanism and increasing the interest-free period.

During the epidemic, major auto companies began to explore the online marketing model and the offline "no contact model" . "Live car broadcast" , "cloud watching car" and "zero contact" opened up a new scene of auto distribution, using the Internet's digital toolbox, car companies began to try to sell cars online.

Although difficult to compare with the outbreak after SARS, but the new pneumonia epidemic period, the public transport restrictions on private cars to enlarge the advantages of safe and private mobile space. Edmund Wilson, a consultancy, said in a report that the shift in pent up demand would encourage first time car buyers to buy cars without a car, and that online demand would rise significantly.

True, most consumers stay at home, but that doesn't stop them from wanting to buy a car.

As a result, auto e-commerce is once again active, unlike in the past, this time more shop sales consultants, began to play online celebrity "Li Jiaqi" , to engage in car with goods.

"If we don't make a breakthrough, we won't be able to eat even the soil, " the host of the event, Fuzhou Furui lincoln-meigui, told the CAIJING reporter. "I never thought that cars could be broadcast live, but I thought that even if I couldn't sell cars, I could do propaganda. " More humor and earnestness on the air led him to build a live broadcast team and a fan base.

Online platform to break the geographical restrictions, which is in the epidemic area of the front-line dealers in Hubei, can be said to be a timely help.

"At the end of the day, most people are forced to do it, " said Muggle Che, an anchorman on the online platform who understands Che di. Below the line is the investor and general manager of an independent brand dealer in Wuhan, Hubei Province, he admitted to the "CAIJING" reporter when the marketing department, sales consultants are embarrassed, he was forced to be "Internet celebrities.

Every day at home, holding a tablet to the audience can not see the model, seven hours a day talking to themselves. From the initial fear of awkward silence, to the imaginary audience in front of the audience, from the audience to walk, to take the initiative with the rhythm. After continuous efforts, intend to say to the customer after unsealing to see the car, keep the user said to repair the car at that time. Interestingly, he also helps fellow dealers in other regions introduce sales leads.

According to Shen Jinjun, President of the China Association of Automobile Dealers, many new marketing methods and formats will emerge as the epidemic wears off. "An event can reshape an entire industry. "

This pattern of restructuring, perhaps not only the car e-commerce or online, online car, the greater opportunity comes from the domestic car manufacturers restructuring and integration.

With the development of China's auto industry, many small and medium-sized auto companies have come into being as the Times require, and have also made money along the trend.

Under the aggravating automobile cold winter, the automobile profession survival of the fittest, each big automobile enterprise's annexation reorganization, the alliance cooperation may carry out more smoothly. It may be cruel, but it is also an opportunity for Chinese cars to grow.
